defs.name: allocate_from_iterator

defs.name: Reallocator

defs.docs:
A matrix reallocator. Changes the size of the memory buffer that initially contains (RFrom ×
 CFrom) elements to a smaller or larger size (RTo, CTo).

defs.name: reallocate_copy
defs.value: fn (nrows: RTo, ncols: CTo, buf: <Self as Allocator<N, RFrom, CFrom>>::Buffer) -> <Self as Allocator<N, RTo, CTo>>::Buffer
defs.docs:
Reallocates a buffer of shape `(RTo, CTo)`, possibly reusing a previously allocated buffer
 `buf`. Data stored by `buf` are linearly copied to the output:

defs.name: axpy

defs.name: gemv
defs.value: fn <R2, C2, D3, SB, SC> (&mut self, alpha: N, a: &Matrix<N, R2, C2, SB>, x: &Vector<N, D3, SC>, beta: N) -> ()
defs.docs:
Computes `self = alpha * a * x + beta * self`, where `a` is a matrix, `x` a vector, and
 `alpha, beta` two scalars.

defs.name: gemv_symm
defs.value: fn <D2, D3, SB, SC> (&mut self, alpha: N, a: &SquareMatrix<N, D2, SB>, x: &Vector<N, D3, SC>, beta: N) -> ()
defs.docs:
Computes `self = alpha * a * x + beta * self`, where `a` is a **symmetric** matrix, `x` a
 vector, and `alpha, beta` two scalars.

defs.name: gemv_tr
defs.value: fn <R2, C2, D3, SB, SC> (&mut self, alpha: N, a: &Matrix<N, R2, C2, SB>, x: &Vector<N, D3, SC>, beta: N) -> ()
defs.docs:
Computes `self = alpha * a.transpose() * x + beta * self`, where `a` is a matrix, `x` a vector, and
 `alpha, beta` two scalars.

defs.name: gemm
defs.value: fn <R2, C2, R3, C3, SB, SC> (&mut self, alpha: N, a: &Matrix<N, R2, C2, SB>, b: &Matrix<N, R3, C3, SC>, beta: N) -> ()
defs.docs:

 `alpha` and `beta` are scalar.

defs.name: gemm_tr
defs.value: fn <R2, C2, R3, C3, SB, SC> (&mut self, alpha: N, a: &Matrix<N, R2, C2, SB>, b: &Matrix<N, R3, C3, SC>, beta: N) -> ()

 `alpha` and `beta` are scalar.

defs.name: try_to_usize
defs.docs:
Gets the compile-time value of `Self`. Returns `None` if it is not known, i.e., if `Self =
 Dynamic`.

defs.name: value
defs.docs:
Gets the run-time value of `self`. For type-level integers, this is the same as
 `Self::try_to_usize().unwrap()`.

defs.name: from_usize
defs.docs:
Builds an instance of `Self` from a run-time value. Panics if `Self` is a type-level
 integer and `dim != Self::try_to_usize().unwrap()`.
